  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Student Care Programme Staff (Teacher)",
  "description": "<p>Job Description</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Working in an After School Care Centre based in MOE Primary Schools.</li>\n  <li>Ensure classroom discipline and safety of children under your care.</li>\n  <li>Need to be responsible and be a good role model for the children.</li>\n  <li>Need to have the passion and love for the children.</li>\n  <li>Committed to working long term.</li>\n  <li>Provide guidance and homework supervision to a class of primary school children (P1-P6) in their homework and spelling.</li>\n  <li>Work effectively and proactively in a dynamic school environment.</li>\n  <li>Conduct in-house program and instill good habits and values.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Job Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Possess genuine care to mentor/guide/work with children in primary schools.</li>\n  <li>WSQ Intro to Student and Youth Care (SCC) certification has added advantage.</li>\n  <li>Experience in school-based student care preferred.</li>\n  <li>Able to discipline students patiently and firmly.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Others</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>We offer an attractive package with good employee benefits, conducive working environment and good career growth.</li>\n  <li>Work-life balance with opportunity to work from home.</li>\n  <li>Remuneration and benefits will commensurate with qualifications and experience.</li>\n</ul>",
